  "text": "Diagnosis: probable JME\n\nInvestigations: EEG 1992: frequent bursts of spike and wave and polyspike\n      \t\tMRI 1993: mild cerebellar atrophy\n\nMedication: lamotrigine 250 milligrams twice a day\nKeppra 1000 milligrams twice a day\n\nFurther to my previous letter I can report that she is doing very well on the above dose of medication. There are no side-effects. She described an episode in clinic of limb shaking with retained consciousness which I don’t think is a seizure. I’d recommend continuing on the same medications and I will review in clinic.\n\n",
